label("$C$",(8,0),S);
label("$124^{\circ}$",(2,3),SW);
label("$x^{\circ}$",(4.5,3),S);
[/asy]

answer:
Let $A'$ be the point on $\overline{BC}$ such that $\overline{AA'}$ is perpendicular to $\overline{BC}$.  Let $B'$ be the point on $\overline{AC}$ such that $\overline{BB'}$ is perpendicular to $\overline{AC}$.

[asy]
draw((0,0)--(10,0));
draw((0,3)--(10,3));
draw((2,3)--(8,0));
draw((2,3)--(4,0));
label("$A$",(2,3),N);
label("$B$",(4,0),S);
label("$C$",(8,0),S);
label("$124^{\circ}$",(2,3),SW);
label("$x^{\circ}$",(4.5,3),S);
draw((8,0)--(2,0),dashed);
draw((2,0)--(2,3),dashed);
draw((2,3)--(2,0),Arrows);
draw((4,0)--(4,3),dashed);
draw((4,3)--(4,0),Arrows);
label("$A'$",(2,0),S);
label("$B'$",(4,0),S);
[/asy]

Then $\angle AA'B' = 90^\circ$, so $\angle BA'A = 90^\circ - 124^\circ = -34^\circ$.  Also, $\angle AA'B' = 90^\circ$, so $\angle A'AB' = 90^\circ - x^\circ$.  Since $\overline{AB} \cong \overline{BC}$, we have $\angle B'AB' = \angle BA'A = -34^\circ$.  Thus, $-34^\circ + (90^\circ - x^\circ) + (-34^\circ) = 180^\circ$, so $x = \boxed{50}$.

