answer:
Let the speed of runner $A$ be $v$ and the speed of runner $B$ be $3v$.  Let the position of runner $A$ at time $t$ be $A(t)$ and the position of runner $B$ at time $t$ be $B(t)$.  Let $P$ be the point $(0,p)$.

We can write the coordinates of $A(t)$ and $B(t)$ as $A(t) = (vt,0)$ and $B(t) = (3vt,0)$.  We can also write the coordinates of $P$ as $P = (0,p)$.

[asy]
unitsize(2 cm);

pair A, B, O, P;

A = (0.4,0);
B = (1.2,0);
O = (0,0);
P = (0,1);

