answer:
Let $A_1$, $A_2$, $\ldots$, $A_7$ be the vertices of the regular heptagon, listed in order.  Then $\angle A_1A_3A_2$ is an interior angle of a regular hexagon, so its measure is $120^\circ$.

[asy]
unitsize(1.5 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E, F, G;

real theta = 360/7;

A = dir(360*3/7 + 90);
B = dir(360*2/7 + 90);
C = A + dir(90)*(dir(360*4/7 + 90) - A);
D = C + dir(90)*(A - C);
E = D + dir(90)*(C - D);
F = E + dir(90)*(D - E);
G = F + dir(90)*(E - F);

pair[] dots = {A, B, C, D, E, F, G};

draw(A--C--E--G--cycle);
draw(B--D--F--cycle);
draw(A--G);
draw(C--F);
draw(E--B);

label("$A_1$", A, A);
label("$A_2$", B, SW);
label("$A_3$", C, SE);
label("$A_4$", D, NE);
label("$A_5$", E, NW);
label("$A_6$", F, SW);
label("$A_7$", G, SE);

dot(dots);
[/asy]

Note that $\triangle A_1A_3A_2$ is isosceles, so $\angle A_2A_1A_3 = 30^\circ$.  Similarly, $\triangle A_3A_5A_4$ is isosceles, so $\angle A_4A_3A_5 = 30^\circ$.

[asy]
unitsize(1.5 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E, F, G;

real theta = 360/7;

A = dir(360*3/7 + 90);
B = dir(360*2/7 + 90);
C = A + dir(90)*(dir(360*4/7 + 90) - A);
D = C + dir(90)*(A - C);
E = D + dir(90)*(C - D);
F = E + dir(90)*(D - E);
G = F + dir(90)*(E - F);

pair[] dots = {A, B, C, D, E, F, G};

draw(A--C--E--G--cycle);
draw(B--D--F--cycle);
draw(A--G);
draw(C--F);
draw(E--B);

label("$A_1$", A, A);
label("$A_2$", B, SW);
label("$A_3$", C, SE);
label("$A_4$", D, NE);
label("$A_5$", E, NW);
label("$A_6$", F, SW);
label("$A_7$", G, SE);

dot(dots);

draw(B--C--D--E--F--G--A--cycle);
[/asy]

Thus, $\angle A_2A_1A_5 = \angle A_2A_1A_3 + \angle A_3A_1A_5 = 30^\circ + 30^\circ = 60^\circ$.

Note that $\angle A_1A_2A_3 = \frac{360^\circ}{7}$.  Also, $\triangle A_1A_2A_3$ is isosceles, so $\angle A_3A_1A_2 = \frac{180^\circ - \frac{360^\circ}{7}}{2} = \frac{255^\circ}{7}$.  Similarly, $\angle A_5A_1A_4 = \frac{255^\circ}{7}$.

[asy]
