answer:
The sum of the interior angles of a regular heptagon is $ (7-2) \times 180^\circ = 900^\circ $, so each interior angle measures $ \frac{900^\circ}{7} $.  The exterior angle $ \angle BAC $ is half the difference between a right angle and an interior angle of the heptagon, so \begin{align*}
\angle BAC &= \frac{1}{2} \left(90^\circ - \frac{900^\circ}{7}\right) \\
&= \frac{1}{2} \left( \frac{630^\circ}{7} - \frac{900^\circ}{7} \right) \\
&= \boxed{\frac{135}{7}^\circ}.
\end{align*}

