Note that
$$|(a + b)(a + c)(a + d)(b + c)(b + d)(c + d)| = |a + b|^2 |a + c|^2 |a + d|^2 |b + c|^2 |b + d|^2 |c + d|^2.$$Also, $|a + b|^2 = (a + b)(\overline{a} + \overline{b}) = 2 + a + \overline{b} + b + \overline{a} = 2 + a + \frac{1}{a} + \frac{1}{a} + \frac{1}{a} = 4 + \frac{a}{a} + \frac{a}{a} + \frac{a}{a} = 4 + a + a + a = 4 + 3a.$ Thus,
$$|(a + b)(a + c)(a + d)(b + c)(b + d)(c + d)| = |4 + 3a|^2 |4 + 3b|^2 |4 + 3c|^2 |4 + 3d|^2.$$We want to maximize this expression subject to the constraints that $a,$ $b,$ $c,$ and $d$ are distinct sixth roots of unity other than $1.$

If $a = w^k,$ then
$$|4 + 3a|^2 = |4 + 3w^k|^2 = (4 + 3w^k)(4 + 3w^{-k}) = 16 + 12(w^k + w^{-k}) + 9 = 25 + 12 \cdot 2 \cos \frac{k \pi}{3} = 25 + 24 \cos \frac{k \pi}{3}.$$Thus, the expression we want to maximize is
$$\prod_{k = 1}^5 (25 + 24 \cos \frac{k \pi}{3}).$$Note that
$$25 + 24 \cos \frac{k \pi}{3} = 25 + 24 \cos \left( \pi - \frac{k \pi}{3} \right) = 25 - 24 \cos \frac{k \pi}{3},$$so
$$\prod_{k = 1}^5 (25 + 24 \cos \frac{k \pi}{3}) = \prod_{k = 1}^5 (25 - 24 \cos \frac{k \pi}{3}).$$Let $P(x) = x^5 + a x^4 + b x^3 + c x^2 + d x + e$ be the polynomial whose roots are $\cos \frac{\pi}{3},$ $\cos \frac{2 \pi}{3},$ $\cos \pi,$ $\cos \frac{4 \pi}{3},$ and $\cos \frac{5 \pi}{3}.$  Then by Vieta's formulas,
$$\prod_{k = 1}^5 (25 - 24 \cos \frac{k \pi}{3}) = 25^5 - 25^4 a + 25^3 b - 25^2 c + 25 d - e.$$From the identity $\cos 5 \theta = 16 \cos^5 \theta - 20 \cos^3 \theta + 5 \cos \theta,$ if $\theta = \frac{k \pi}{3},$ then $\cos 5 \theta = -1,$ so
$$16 \cos^5 \theta - 20 \cos^3 \theta + 5 \cos \theta + 1 = 0.$$Thus, $P(x) = 16x^5 - 20x^3 + 5x + 1,$ so
$$\prod_{k = 1}^5 (25 - 24 \cos \frac{k \pi}{3}) = 25^5 - 25^4 \cdot \frac{-20}{16} + 25^3 \cdot 0 - 25^2 \cdot \frac{5}{16} - 25 \cdot \frac{1}{16} - 1 = \boxed{14400000}.$$

