answer:
Let $x = \angle BAC.$  Since $\triangle ABC$ is isosceles, the base angles are both $180^\circ - 2x,$ so
$$\angle BDC = 3x = 180^\circ - 2(180^\circ - 2x) = 4x - 180^\circ.$$Then $x = 60^\circ.$  Hence, $\angle BDC = 180^\circ - 60^\circ = 120^\circ.$

[asy]
unitsize(0.4 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, M;

A = (0,11);
D = (0,1);
