The length of $AB$ is
$$\sqrt{(2 - 0)^2 + (\sqrt{2} - \sqrt{2})^2} = 2,$$and the length of $CD$ is also 2.  Hence, the area of $ABCD$ is $\frac{1}{2} \cdot 2 \cdot 2 = \boxed{2}.$

